text: This looks awesome and a step up from the 1st. By the looks of it, it has elements of the obvious Rocky IV but also Rocky III with 2 points that are seen in the trailer. The first being like Mickey, Rocky doesnt believe he can beat 'this guy' if that is Drago or Wheeler who knows. The second is that unlike Rocky who HAD to train with Apollo at his gym after Mickey died, Adonis CHOOSES to train there after Rocky has no belief he can win.   I can also see a Rocky vs Drago fight happening but not how everyone thinks. I actually think we see what we never saw before with Rocky and Apollo and that is a secret fight behind closed doors that will also like in Rocky III be captured with a painting that will ultimately lead to being displayed alongside the Apollo version and also the Rocky Statue at the end of the film because like Mickey, Stallone will finally hang up his gloves and let Rocky Balboa pass away. At the funeral will be Adonis and wife, Apollos wife, Little Duke (Apollos trainers son) , The Drago's who eventually become friends and last but not least he will be buried alongside Adrian and Paulie.   As for a CREED III i think they will follow suit with Rocky 3 and bring in a guy similar BUT NOT a Lang. Who should be portrayed as a complete violent and sadistic slugger who is also an ex-con who spent 10 years in prison for manslaughter. That should make audiences want to go see the film without Stallone being involved in the film and make it as close as possible to a R rating or make it R rated and if its R rated let Stallone direct as he did Rambo 4 which was bloody and violent AF exactly how a Rambo movie should of been.

text: Rocky IV has always been my favorite guilty pleasure and one of the best escapist experience for me. I do not remember how many times I've seen Rocky IV and how many times I've paid rent for its VHS tape in 90's. Not only this I've listened its OST from its training montage during my gym time and still stays top in my play list if I'm giving my time to gym. Very motivational. Makers of Rocky IV now bringing toughest boxer on silver screen Ivan Draggo back in CREED II. Story of CREED II is very interesting and raise maximum level of curiosity to know more when we come to know that Adonis Johnson the son of late boxer Apollo Creed tests himself in the boxing ring against Victor Draggo son of Ivan Draggo who is trained by his father and Adnois Johnson requests Rocky Balboa to train him against Victor Draggo. If you have watched Rocky IV then just imagine the characters and story will unravel in your mind itself. Amazing story line and no doubt movie to watch this year. I do not know about others but I'm very excited and going to watch this film on cinema hall. CREED II

text: I really don't see the need for this after *Creed* satisfyingly concluded Rocky's story while leaving the imagination open for him to pass the torch to a new generation. Adonis already proved himself, his arc of overcoming his past seemed finished.   I personally felt that was a near-perfect series ending. I'm just worried that, as with countless other franchises, this new saga will make the same mistake the *Rocky* films did by dragging it out too long (This already looks like a rehash of *3).*  It's also honestly rather silly that a relative of Drago's would enter to challenge Adonis, that's an almost crazy-small world. text: I remember seeing Creed for my first date with my boyfriend (who am I still with) while it was in theaters. I am a big fan of the Rocky movies (maybe not so much the 5th one) and I hated Creed. I came in expecting to love it, so excited to see the continuation of one of my favorite series and left awfully dissapointed. I realise this movie isn't about Rocky (which I see is the reason why a lot of people dislike the film), but I felt like the story and plot was truly weak. There was nothing special about it, it's been seen before, except other times they did it better. I wish I could have loved Creed, but I'll always remember it as my awful first date experience with my long time boyfriend.

text: I have a notion that we just seen a spoiler perhaps... when Creed is walking into what seems like the fight with Drago, Rocky is not by his side. I'm thinking this is it for Rocky (although I love every bit of Rocky even Rocky V) and Sly has made the decision to let Rocky die from the cancer he was fighting in Creed 1. This is the 8th time Rocky Balboa is on the big screen. Stallone wanted to end Rocky in part 5 and didn't then he said at the end of Creed when Rocky reached the top of the steps and said "You can see your whole life from up here" was a good send-off... he then stated he would not be in Creed II. I'm incredibly excited he's back again but feel this is it for ole' Rock. Creed will go on to fight Drago for not only his father but for his "Unc" Rocky. Stallone writing and directing this makes me think this that much more. Looking forward to seeing Dolph and Rocky face to face again on the big screen. This is EVERYTHING I wanted for a sequel. If Rocky lives through the movie then AWESOME! Creed III can be his curtain call. I can't wait for November now!

text: Having watched this trailer about 20 times...I've finally pieced my theory of the film together. Donnie wins the light heavyweight title. The guy he's punching at 1:30 is Danny "Stuntman" Wheeler (aka Andre Ward), the man Conlan was supposed to face in the first movie to unify the belts and the WBA/WBC and Ring Magazine champion. Basically, the #1 guy in the sport in Conlan's absence. So logically, Creed beats him and wins his titles.  Viktor Drago emerges as a contender and Rocky immediately hesitates for obvious reasons, refusing to train him. Donnie instead is trained at the Delphi Gym by Lil Duke and gets knocked out by Drago. Or, Rocky stopped training him altogether and it's been Lil Duke training him all along. That's the first part of the trailer though...KO'd, getting the light shined to check his faculties and then in the hospital. Another clue is the part where he puts on his glasses. Lil Duke is standing behind him and if you slow the video down, you can see photo flashes. It's almost like a post fight press conference. Especially since Donnie is lumped up pretty good in the face. The third and final clue...look closely at 0:02 and slow it down, as Donnie's going down, you can see his opponents gloves are black. At the very end of the trailer, when Drago is hitting him at 1:53...he's got red gloves on. Two fights.   Donnie wants to fight him again and convinces Rocky to train him to avenge his loss as well as his father.    LET'S GO!

text: As much as people trash anything past Rocky 2, the 4th one, despite all it's flaws I see as a young adult, made me starstruck. I wanted to become a boxer and learn how to fight in general but my father wouldn't allow me to do so. Now, I'm almost 4 years deep into martial arts and finally doing it, and I'm so pumped for this movie. I feel like things are coming full circle in little ways like this in my life. So if you're reading this, it is not merely a cliche statement: your heart and mind are telling you to do something, you do it with every fiber of your being. There will be setbacks, but persevere, and become a champion. I wish you well and maybe I'll see you at the premiere of this bad boy!

text: This is a really good trailer. Going back to the first Creed movie, I think what really makes it work other than Michael B Jordan being a very talented actor and Stallone really submitting an understated very strong performance as well, is that they know exactly how to use the history of the series. for instance they really Drew back perfectly to the time when Apollo was telling Rocky that he didn't have a choice, that he had to fight because he was a warrior because he didn't know another way to live. We saw the result of that ehen he got killed in the ring, so because of that it resonate even more when his son he never even met but clearly inherited his nature quotes him so directly, and Rocky has to face the last time he had this conversation because the last time it happened it resulted in somebody's death.  The other really good parallel is Rocky talking to Mickey in the third movie and Mickey telling him straight up you can't win against Clubber Lang, although this time they flipped it around a little bit and it's Adonis accusing Rocky of not believing in him. That little part of the trailer works so well, and I think it's the best part of the trailer because you can see the hurt on his face knowing that the one person who supposed to believe in him above all seems to not have that belief. Of course, he's misinterpreting genuine concern as doubt. We've seen this before, and so the effect is twofold. It's obviously pretty crushing to him. Long story short, I want to see how this plays out.

text: In my mind before the film: Drago's son is only fighting Adonis to prove to his father, Ivan, that he's not a failure. Something like Adonis went through in the the 1st Creed film.  While, Ivan is still holding so much anger for losing to Rocky, making it personal. Maybe even hate guilt for killing Adonis dad, Apollo.  Yet, Adonis wants revenge and proving that he has what it takes to be the greatest, even if it means fighting his father's killer's son. A personal vendetta.  Lastly, Rocky is still by Adonis no matter any obstacle. Since Adonis reminds Rocky of what it's like still to fight for something, while still developing a father-son relationship. Even in reality its sad that Sylvester's son died, leaving him an empty emotional love-care for a son. In my view, Rocky sees Adonis as his son.  In my mind for the ending of the film: I only hope Drago's son can be much more than his Father, Ivan. While, Ivan can learn to accept his defeat and possibly make amends to both Rocky and Adonis. While, Adonis becomes the right role model for many fighters, even being a father too. Lastly, Rocky will be thanked and forgiven by Mary-Ann for being the right person needed every time for Adonis, as a father, rather than being a trainer.

text: Seen this film twice now, and freaking loved it both times. Really awesome film. Go see it. You know I‚Äôve already started thinking about what they should do for Creed 3 (which I really hope they make) and i don‚Äôt mean like all the silly comments Creed vs Clubber Lang‚Äôs son or daughter or anything like that. I‚Äôve been thinking how can they step it up emotionally? Because this an incredibly emotional film, like most of the Rocky movies, it‚Äôs a character Drama as much as a Boxing film, and here we have a really good reason for it to because I mean Adonis is facing the son of the man who killed his Father. Now how do we level up from that? How about this, what if we find out that Donny‚Äôs mother had another son, not with Apollo, but with another man, and this Son got lost in the system whereas we know Donny got rescued by Mary Anne. So here we have this long lost brother, who see‚Äôs his little brother basically renouncing their mother‚Äôs name, and sitting pretty with a wife, kid, new mom, and new surrogate father in Rocky, so now this resentment is starting to build, so he works and works and works to challenge Adonis for the Heavyweight title in an effort to break him down and take away the things that matter most to him.
